<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1194,1365]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
This is the only Neotropical Ophiderini with orange-yellow hindwings lacking a medial patch. As in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1867" box="[1309,1394,1267,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Tetrisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1309,1394,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Tetrisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the forewings do not have a tornal hook. Specimens or photos have been examined from 
<collectingCountry box="[1119,1207,1303,1329]" name="Mexico" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1220,1294,1303,1329]" name="Belize" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Belize</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1306,1432,1303,1329]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,243,1339,1365]" name="Panama" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Panama</collectingCountry>
, Columbia, 
<collectingCountry box="[378,463,1339,1365]" name="Bolivia" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, French Guiana, and 
<collectingCountry box="[702,770,1339,1365]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[785,1019,1339,1365]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Santa Catarina State</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
